  "name": "Call Shadow Mastiff",
  "desc": "You conjure a [shadow mastiff](https://api.open5e.com/monsters/shadow-mastiff) from the plane of shadow. This creature obeys your verbal commands to aid you in battle or to seek out a specific creature. It has the body of a large dog with a smooth black coat, 2 feet high at the shoulder and weighing 200 pounds.\n\nThe mastiff is friendly to you and your companions. Roll initiative for the mastiff; it acts on its own turn. It obeys simple, verbal commands from you, within its ability to act. Giving a command takes no action on your part.\n\nThe mastiff disappears when it drops to 0 hit points or when the spell ends.",
